### Welcome

This marks the beginning of a long-term engineering journey focused on developing the skills, projects, and practical experience required for a career in **DevSecOps** and **Secure Infrastructure Engineering**.

Over the next ~16 months, I will follow a structured, project-driven roadmap designed to build strong foundations in systems, infrastructure, automation, cloud technologies, and security. The emphasis will be on practical implementation, real-world projects, and continuous improvement rather than simply completing courses or collecting certifications.

The roadmap is organized into the following phases:

1. Linux Foundations & Administration
2. Networking Fundamentals & Applied Cryptography
3. Scripting & Automation
4. Infrastructure as Code (IaC) & Containers
5. Cloud Engineering (AWS)
6. Observability & Monitoring
7. Security Engineering
8. Kubernetes & Secrets Management
9. Capstone Infrastructure Projects
10. Product Development & Deployment

This blog will serve as a technical journal documenting progress, challenges, lessons learned, project milestones, and key takeaways throughout the journey.

The objective is simple: build real competence, create meaningful projects, and develop the capabilities required to design, automate, secure, and operate modern infrastructure at scale.
